headline: Saudia Group Selects GE Aerospace GEnx-1B Engines to Power New 787 Dreamliners
summary: Saudia Group, one of the largest aviation conglomerates in the MENA region, has announced a strategic agreement with GE Aerospace (NYSE: GE) to equip Saudia, the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia's national flag carrier, with GEnx-1B engines for its 2023 order of 39 Boeing 787-9 and 787-10 aircraft. The agreement includes the supply of engines, a multi-year maintenance, repair, and overhaul (MRO) program, and spare engines. headline: Oracle and Other AI Stocks Are Spending Too Much Money. These Companies Are Returning Cash in Spades.
summary: Since the end of October, companies returning relatively large amounts of cash to shareholders through dividends and buybacks have seen their stocks outperform others.
